@layout('layout-docs')
<h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Validation</h1>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">Nimbus provides a <strong>VineJS-inspired fluent validation API</strong> for validating requests, forms, and models. Define rules as chainable methods, validate structs directly, and use database-backed rules for uniqueness checks.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-2">Fluent schema rules</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-2">Define validation schemas using the fluent builder API:</p>
<pre><code>import "github.com/CodeSyncr/nimbus/validation"

func (r *CreateBlogRequest) Rules() validation.Schema {
    return validation.Schema{
        "title":   validation.String().Required().Min(1).Max(255),
        "content": validation.String().Required().Min(1).Max(5000),
        "email":   validation.String().Required().Email(),
        "age":     validation.Number().Required().Min(18).Max(120),
    }
}</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-2">String rules</h2>
<div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
  <table class="min-w-full text-sm text-slate-700 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg">
    <thead class="bg-slate-50"><tr><th class="px-4 py-2 text-left font-semibold">Method</th><th class="px-4 py-2 text-left font-semibold">Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Required()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Field must not be empty</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Min(n)</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Minimum length</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Max(n)</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Maximum length</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Email()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Must be a valid email</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">URL()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Must be a valid URL</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Regex(pattern)</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Must match regex</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">In(values...)</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Must be one of the allowed values</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Alpha()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Letters only</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">AlphaNum()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Letters and numbers only</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Trim()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Trim whitespace before validation</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Confirmed()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Must match <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">field_confirmation</code></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-2">Number rules</h2>
<div class="overflow-x-auto mb-4">
  <table class="min-w-full text-sm text-slate-700 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg">
    <thead class="bg-slate-50"><tr><th class="px-4 py-2 text-left font-semibold">Method</th><th class="px-4 py-2 text-left font-semibold">Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Required()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Field must not be zero</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Min(n)</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Minimum value</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Max(n)</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Maximum value</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Positive()</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Must be greater than 0</td></tr>
      <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="px-4 py-2"><code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Between(min, max)</code></td><td class="px-4 py-2">Must be within range</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-2">Database rules</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-2">Use <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Unique()</code> and <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Exists()</code> for database-backed validation. These query the database using GORM.</p>
<pre><code>func (r *CreateUserRequest) Rules() validation.Schema {
    return validation.Schema{
        // Check email is unique in users table
        "email": validation.String().Required().Email().Unique(validation.UniqueOpts{
            Table:  "users",
            Column: "email",
        }),

        // Unique with filter (exclude current user during updates)
        "email": validation.String().Required().Email().Unique(validation.UniqueOpts{
            Table:  "users",
            Column: "email",
            Filter: func(db *gorm.DB) *gorm.DB {
                return db.Where("id != ?", currentUserID)
            },
        }),

        // Check role exists in roles table
        "role_id": validation.Number().Required().Exists(validation.ExistsOpts{
            Table:  "roles",
            Column: "id",
        }),
    }
}</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-2">Model-level validation</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-2">Models can implement <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">SchemaProvider</code> to validate themselves. This is the recommended pattern:</p>
<pre><code>type Todo struct {
    database.Model
    Title string
    Done  bool
}

func (t *Todo) Rules() validation.Schema {
    return validation.Schema{
        "title": validation.String().Required().Min(1).Max(255),
    }
}

func (t *Todo) Validate() error {
    return validation.ValidateStruct(t)
}

// In a controller:
todo := &models.Todo{Title: strings.TrimSpace(ctx.Request.FormValue("title"))}
if err := todo.Validate(); err != nil {
    return ctx.View("form", map[string]any{"error": err.Error()})
}</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-2">Request validation in controllers</h2>
<pre><code>func (c *BlogController) Store(ctx *http.Context) error {
    var req validators.CreateBlogRequest

    ve, err := validation.BindAndValidateSchema(ctx, &req)
    if ve != nil {
        return ve  // returns 422 JSON with validation errors
    }
    if err != nil {
        return err
    }

    blog := &models.Blog{Title: req.Title, Content: req.Content}
    if err := database.Get().Create(blog).Error; err != nil {
        return err
    }
    return ctx.JSON(http.StatusCreated, blog)
}</code></pre>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-2">Generating validators</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-2">Scaffold a validator with the CLI:</p>
<pre><code>nimbus make:validator Blog</code></pre>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">This generates a struct with <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Rules()</code> and <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Validate()</code> methods using the fluent API.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-8 mb-2">Conditional validation</h2>
<p class="text-slate-600 mb-2">Apply rules conditionally based on another field's value or a custom predicate:</p>

<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-2">When (field-based)</h3>
<pre><code>func (r *CreateUserRequest) Rules() validation.Schema {
    return validation.Schema{
        "role":       validation.String().Required().In("personal", "business", "creator"),
        // Only required when role is "business"
        "company_id": validation.When("role", "business", validation.String().Required()),
        // Only required when role is "creator", with a fallback otherwise
        "bio": validation.When("role", "creator", validation.String().Min(10)).
            Otherwise(validation.String().Max(500)),
    }
}</code></pre>

<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-2">WhenFn (predicate-based)</h3>
<pre><code>func (r *OrderRequest) Rules() validation.Schema {
    return validation.Schema{
        "shipping_address": validation.WhenFn(
            func(data map[string]any) bool {
                return data["delivery_type"] == "physical"
            },
            validation.String().Required().Min(10),
        ),
    }
}</code></pre>

<p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 text-sm">Conditional rules implement the <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 rounded">Rule</code> interface and compose naturally with other rules in the schema.</p>
